 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=glasya7>Glasya7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 281<br> <font color=#333333>(11/22/02 8:06:23 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Gallerus</span><hr size=1> Necromancers are the masters of soloing hands down.  The dark spells that do large damage, they get lure based (FR -100) blood-line DOT spells, almost unresistable (MR -200) leech-line DOT spells, almost unresistable taps, lure-like splurt, poison DOTs, disease DOTs...  then they get fear, feign death, harmshield, root, mez (ST), gate, self evac (levant)...  Mana regen withg lich-line off spells.  With fear they can solo MOBs that summon.  It's hard to compare necro's ability to solo with other classes, that's what they were made for, they offer little in term of group buffs.<br>
<br>
Their damage may not be as quick as a mage, but their DOTs are efficient for doing big damage over time and they regen the mana quickly while using leech-line and taps to recharge health.  It's not an easy class to play, but a powerful one.  Admittedly I can do way more damage with a mage and epic, but I don't remember any time when I could solo anything yellow or red, which is trivial with a necro, can kill things up to 5 levels higher as long as they don't summon.<br>
<br>
This topic can't answer who is the best soloer.  There is no right answer it depends on situation.  The issue is whether the fight is outdoors or indoors (druids and necros are not very good indoors).  While a shaman may be good at taking down tough MOBs, a shaman can't clear a dungeon full of mid-level greens as a mage can (this is still soloing, just not for xp, maybe for items).  Druids and wizards can quad kite but if something is not snareable or resist snare they have a hard time; they also can't kite indoors (there are few spots where they can, but that's not the norm).<br>
<br>
The debate of who is the best soloer has to involve a defining of the situation, otherwise it becomes a class envy contest.<br>
