<br>
Unfortunately that isn't true.  Bard soloing is almost non-existant indoors, as is the druid and wizard variety.  Forget fear kiting as well.  <br>
<br>
The only problem a mage has soloing in a dungeon is keeping the size of the pulls reasonable.<br>
<br>
Just about every class has some really cool tools.  For the mage, it's about making stuff dead.  When you can pull a mob in, sick a pet on it, med for a minute and a half, then stand up and blow the beast to shreds, I don't see how you can say mages suck, either at soloing or grouping.<br>
