Now, had you said they suck soloing post-60, I would have to agree.  But then, any class without good movement control spells sucks trying to solo post-60 as well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=etadanikm>EtadanikM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#333333>(11/23/02 12:51:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Agree with everything Glasya said</span><hr size=1> PoP in general is not a very solo friendly place.  The all-revered necro fear-kiting tactics don't work there, nor are there any undead necros can charm in most zones for charm-soloing (enchanters, however, have a ball in PoP).  Yes, necros/druids/wizards/shamans can solo PoP, but I can tell you presently that soloing nets you less exp than a good group (unless you're a truly uber player grouping with newbies), even if you're soloing red-at-60 mobs because of resist issues and whatnot.  <br>
<br>
This is why many necros have been pushing for better grouping abilities, because necro soloing, while viable in PoP, isn't really an alternative to groups because progression in PoP is based on groups, not on soloing.<br>
<br>
