 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=glasya7>Glasya7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 283<br> <font color=#333333>(11/23/02 1:06:44 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Agree with everything Glasya said</span><hr size=1> I've been agro kiting in PoP, usually CD/BoD/CoC/Plague/EB, wait 15 seconds then send pet without taunt and just move around while the MOB walks after you, when CoC wears off, CD again and wait about 12 sec and CoC again.  Nothing adds agro like CoC (which unfortunately won't stack with splurt).<br>
<br>
As a mage I have to rely on a pocket cleric in PoP, most MOBs that hit around 200 need 1 CH to kill, up to 300 may take 2 CHs, things hitting harder than 300 is a lot for an epic to handle. Must debuff everything to make sure the pet can land the stun proc which reduces the MOB dps significantly.<br>
<br>
With PoP the mage's ability to solo has deteriorated, whereas other classes that have any kind of snare ability has remained the same.  The problem with mage pets is that their mitigation skills are poor (all except epic which is so far the best tank for planes).<br>
<br>
On the other hand, the epic can solo all of LGuk, even taking few frogs at a time with a 52 heal every so often.  Necro pet has a very hard time tanking by comparisson.<br>
<br>
One of the most devastating combo's in PoP so far is grouping of a necro and a mage, there is almost no downtime and things die very fast.<br>
