<br>
Mages act like DPS is ALL that matters. And then they go on to say &quot;Blah, we're second in DPS, blah, in some conditions we, blah, if I can posistion my pet...&quot; - BIG DEAL. We're second by what - 5DPS? Some other marginal number? How close is the 3rd, and how many MORE abilities do they have besides DPS? What preconditions does that damage rely on?<br>
<br>
Besides, arguments like this can't be proven. I'm betting you're using 60+ spells to come up with that &quot;#2 in DPS&quot; statement.<br>
<br>
The old DPS argument, as if that's the only thing that matters! OKAY, perhaps in the Mages case - but if so, why are we second? If DPS IS all that matters, shouldn't we rule that area? If not, shouldn't we have SOME utility function that works (CoH, bleh!) AND is sought after? Give me any class and I'll give you 2 things they do good, probably more, in addition to doing an acceptable DPS. Give me the mage and I can give you ONE thing they TRY and do good. And oh! It takes 60 levels to get to &quot;second place.&quot; Dare I fathom the trip there?<br>
<br>
Lots of classes have awesome DPS, in addition to being useful. (And here's where you say &quot;Go play that class then!&quot; - which, I currently am.)<br>
<br>
Bottom Line: Is this class WORTH playing for 60 levels to MAYBE get 2nd place in DPS, with absolutely no other function.<br>
<br>
Before you continue to call me a gimp or whatever (I don't think I've insulted anyone a single time? No matter...) keep in mind that I'm not entirely stubborn and will listen to reasonable rebuttles. Then again, who wants to take the time to do that! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
