As a damage class, it seems to me that, at the very least, DPS is most of what matters.  Personally, I tend to invite mages to my groups more for their DPS than, say, their pick locks skill, heals or tanking ability.  I've not found mages to be terribly effective at porting or evacing, either.  Personally I think they are just lazy.<br>
<br>
To be honest, most of the game is about three things: DPS, aggro management/crowd control and healing.  Mages are badass at the DPS thing.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>and how many MORE abilities do they have besides DPS?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Depends... are we talking about rangers, monks or rogues?  That rogue sneak thing is really useful... all those times that you need rogue CR these days.  Monks have FD/mend... in case a pull goes wrong (though CoH is just as effective of a solution).  Rangers have snare... which is nice.  Doesn't really make a huge difference these days... but no big.  They have some decent buffs.<br>
<br>
Versus... CoH (which, used properly, can spare a group quite a few unnecessary deaths and downtime)?  T-Rods (which provide some helpful emergency mana/additional mana regen)?  To be honest, 9 times out of 10, I'll take take CoH over Sneak/Pick locks.  And as often as not, I'll take a mage over a ranger/monk... depends on the ranger/monk and on the mage.<br>
<br>
What's more, they place <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>little to no strain</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> on the other members of the group (being almost completely self-sufficient), further maximizing their contribution.  (Neither mages nor pets typically require heals or combat-related buffs.)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If DPS IS all that matters, shouldn't we rule that area?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I'm hoping, by quoting this, you see how silly it sounds.<br>
<br>
DPS is the primary goal of several classes.  This does not mean that each of those classes should &quot;rule that area.&quot;  What it means is that, all other things being equal, different ones will &quot;rule&quot; in different situations.  <br>
<br>
In <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>high DPS <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>right now</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> situations, wizards will beat out mages, but mages will have DPS to contribute for the next fight.  In <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>sustained</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> DPS situations, mages, rogues, rangers and monks will be in similar situations... depending on mob ACs, resists, buffs and equipment.  <br>
<br>
The great things about mages is that a good mage is an excellent damage dealer <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>in almost every situation</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  <br>
 <p>Master Maldisdain Atheist<br>
